---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

const lastUpdated = 'May 17, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="What cookies and tracking technologies SaaSStatsHub uses, why, and how to control them."
>
  <article class="max-w-[740px] mx-auto px-6 py-12 article-body">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-8 font-mono">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <p>
      This Cookie Policy explains how SaaSStatsHub uses cookies and similar technologies on
      <a href="https://saasstatshub.com">saasstatshub.com</a>. It supplements our
      <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 id="what">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small text files placed on your device by websites you visit. They are widely used to
      make sites work, work more efficiently, and provide information to site owners. Similar
      technologies include local storage, session storage, web beacons, and pixel tags. We refer to all
      of these collectively as "cookies" in this policy.
    </p>

    <h2 id="categories">2. Categories We Use</h2>
    <p>We group cookies into three categories. Required (strictly necessary) cookies cannot be disabled because the site cannot work without them. Optional cookies (analytics, advertising) are loaded only after you grant consent if you are in a region that requires opt-in (EEA, UK, California).</p>

    <h3>2.1 Strictly necessary</h3>
    <p>Required for the site to function and to comply with security policies. Do not require consent.</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Provider</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Expiry</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>__cf_bm</code></td>
          <td>Cloudflare</td>
          <td>Bot management - distinguishes humans from automated requests.</td>
          <td>30 minutes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>cf_clearance</code></td>
          <td>Cloudflare</td>
          <td>Records that you have completed a security challenge (only set after a challenge).</td>
          <td>30 days</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>saasstatshub_cookie_consent</code></td>
          <td>SaaSStatsHub</td>
          <td>Remembers your cookie preferences so the consent banner is not shown on every visit.</td>
          <td>6 months</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>2.2 Analytics (optional)</h3>
    <p>Help us understand which pages are popular and how the site performs. Loaded only after consent in regions that require opt-in. IP addresses are anonymized.</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Provider</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Expiry</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>_ga</code></td>
          <td>Google Analytics 4</td>
          <td>Distinguishes unique users.</td>
          <td>2 years</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>_ga_&lt;ID&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Google Analytics 4</td>
          <td>Maintains session state for our property.</td>
          <td>2 years</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>2.3 Advertising (optional, when enabled)</h3>
    <p>
      If we display advertising via Google AdSense, additional cookies may be set by Google to serve
      and measure ads. Loaded only after consent in opt-in regions.
    </p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Provider</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Expiry</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>__gads</code>, <code>__gpi</code></td>
          <td>Google AdSense</td>
          <td>Ad selection, frequency capping, fraud prevention.</td>
          <td>13 months</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>NID</code>, <code>IDE</code></td>
          <td>Google</td>
          <td>Ad personalization across Google services.</td>
          <td>up to 24 months</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>
      You can opt out of personalized ads at
      <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>
      regardless of the consent state on this site.
    </p>

    <h2 id="local-storage">3. Local Storage and Similar</h2>
    <p>
      Our on-site search (Pagefind) caches its index in your browser's HTTP cache only. It does not
      use cookies, localStorage, or sessionStorage. Newsletter forms do not set any cookies on submission.
    </p>

    <h2 id="control">4. How to Control Cookies</h2>

    <h3>4.1 On this site</h3>
    <p>
      The first time you visit, you may see a cookie consent banner (if you are in the EEA, UK,
      California, or another region with opt-in requirements). You can change your choice at any time by
      clicking <button id="reset-cookie-consent" class="text-primary underline" type="button">Reset cookie preferences</button>.
    </p>

    <h3>4.2 In your browser</h3>
    <p>
      Most browsers allow you to view, manage, and delete cookies. Instructions for major browsers:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chrome</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/clear-cookies-and-site-data-firefox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Firefox</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Safari</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Edge</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Disabling all cookies will not break this site, but the consent banner will reappear on every
      visit because we cannot remember your choice.
    </p>

    <h3>4.3 Privacy signals we honor</h3>
    <p>
      We honor the Global Privacy Control (GPC) signal as a valid opt-out request from California
      residents under the CCPA. Browsers like Brave and Firefox can be configured to send GPC; some
      extensions add it to other browsers.
    </p>

    <h2 id="changes">5. Changes to this Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Cookie Policy as we add or remove services. The "Last updated" date at the top
      reflects the latest revision.
    </p>

    <h2 id="contact">6. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Privacy / cookie questions:
      <a href="mailto:sangaypopo@gmail.com">sangaypopo@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  // Allow users to reset their cookie consent from inside the policy page.
  document.getElementById('reset-cookie-consent')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    try {
      localStorage.removeItem('saasstatshub_cookie_consent');
      document.cookie = 'saasstatshub_cookie_consent=; expires=Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 GMT; path=/';
    } catch {}
    location.reload();
  });
</script>
